dismissalText.long: c Kamran Akmal b Umar Gul
dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons c Kamran Akmal b Umar Gul 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Simmons debut ends in a tragedy. He lasted just two balls. He was tempted by a good-length delivery in that channel, poked at it with an open-face of the bat and the resultant edge was picked up by Akmal low to his right.

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle c Inzamam-ul-Haq b Naved-ul-Hasan 0 (4b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: What a start for Pakistan! Chris Gayle falls. Big wicket. Full and it swung in a bit, Gayle pushes at it defensively, but ends up pushing the bat inside the line, and the outside edge flew low to the left of Inzamam at first slip and he gobbled it up. It was a outswinger to the right-hand bat, and Gayle spotted it and played it accordingly but this one didn't swing in so much as he anticipated and hence he ended up playing in the wrong line.

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin run out (Umar Gul/Kamran Akmal) 23 (35b 1x4 1x6 55m) SR: 65.71

dismissalComment.html: played away through midwicket. Ramdin calls for the second and sprints across - Umar Gul hurtles across in the deep and fires in a brilliant throw at the striker's end - Akmal moves in front of the stumps, collects the ball cleanly and drags it into the stumps.&

dismissalText.commentary: Ian Bradshaw run out (Mohammad Hafeez) 3 (7b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: tapped away towards backward point and they scamper through for a single - Hafeez moves in quickly, the pick-up is spot on and he hits the bowler's stumps with clinical precision - Bradshaw is history

headshotImage.longCaption: Corey Collymore player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: and Inzi finishes it off it style - short delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Inzi rocks back and pulls it away well wide of the fielder at short fine leg. There is no protection in the deep and the ball rolls over the ropes - crowd goes berzerk

commentPostTextItems.html: Another splendid performance from the big man has seen Pakistan through. Unruffled, despite all the commotion around him, he finished his job in style. After making a dismal 151 West Indies regrouped well to come back strongly, and if it was not for the solid presence of Inzamam they might have pulled off a coup. We will be back on Decemeber 10th with the live coverage of the third one-dayer, until then this is Sajan Nair along with Sriram Veera signing off - good night, and good luck.

commentTextItems.html: good length delivery on the pads and Rao neatly turns it away towards fine leg for a single.
not again! quicker delivery outside the off stump and the edge rolls away well wide of the fielder at gully.

commentTextItems.html: driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
drifting down the leg side, Rao fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad
tossed up outside the off stump, Rao drives well  - diving stop by the fielder at cover cuts off the single. Tension mounts and the crowd is dead silent
full and on the stumps, punched down to mid-on
good length delivery, turning in - Rao gets forward and defends it with a straight bat
good length delivery outside the off stump, Rao gets well forward and punches it away through cover point.

commentPostTextItems.html: It was an easy single alright that run will keep Inzi away from the strike. One more wicket here now will surely give West Indies the upper hand.

commentPostTextItems.html: Two wickets - 5 runs. What is it going to be?

commentTextItems.html: good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, played away towards point
short delivery outside the off stump and Rehman leaves it through to the keeper - setting him up for the fuller one?
short rising delivery on the stumps. Rehman gets right on top of the bounce and defends it down into the track. Well played - Inzi walks down the track and has a word with the youngester

commentPreTextItems.html: Taylor the hat-trick man into the attack now - can he do it again?

commentTextItems.html: almost! short of a good length delivery, in the channel and slanting away - Rehman plays inside the line and the ball zips past the outside edge
fulltoss on the pads and Rehman punches it down to wide long-on

commentPostTextItems.html: Just five needed now with three wickets in hand - Bye Bye West Indies?

commentTextItems.html: good length delivery outside the off stump - Inzi walks into the shot and drives it down to long-off - just 6 more needed now
cut away late - diving stop by Smith at short third man saves runs but fails to cut off the single
driven on the up towards cover, straight to Lara there
punched down to long-on and he walks across as if he is having a early morning walk - what a player.
driven away towards cover
